The paper proposes a novel approach for unsupervised feature selection based on subspace clustering and similarity learning. This involves representation learning of low dimensional subspaces among the samples and the use of a self-expressive model to implicitly learn cluster similarities in an adaptive manner. These techniques are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision, which suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG, cs.CV, or cs.AI sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CL or cs.DM sub-categories.
